    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-09-23T16:01:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-09-23T16:01:00-05:00" n="274"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of Defense files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss> to the
                        Commander in Chief Far East (<persName corresp="#p_CGMW1" type="to"
                            >Clark</persName>) and the Commander in Chief Pacific (<persName
                            corresp="#p_RAAW1">Radford</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>operational immediate</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-09-23T17:01:00-04:00"
                            >September 23, 1952—5:01 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 919187. From <gloss target="#t_JCS1"
                        >JCS</gloss>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> are considering possible future opns in
                        Far East in event present negots fail to produce armistice. <gloss
                            target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> recognize that it may <pb facs="0562"
                            n="528" xml:id="pg_528"/> become advisable to recommend removal of all
                        restrictions now currently in force except: <list>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Attacks on the USSR proper.</item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Use of atomic or <gloss target="#t_CW1">CW</gloss> weapons other
                                than as now authorized.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Courses of action being considered include: <list>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Amphibious, airborne, or ground offensives to increase pressure on
                                enemy and possibly secure the waist or other areas of Korea.</item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Air attacks on airdrome complexes.</item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Blockade of China proper with coordinated air attacks on transp
                                centers (refers only to Para 3, Case III below).</item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Air attacks on comm centers in north and central China and in
                                Manchuria.</item>
                            <label>
                                <hi rend="italic">e</hi>.</label>
                            <item>Combinations or variations of actions outlined above.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss> comments, coordinated with <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> as appropriate, are desired on
                        courses of action outlined above under folg three alternative assumptions as
                        to force availability: <list>
                            <item>Case I. Forces now available to <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1"
                                    >CINCFE</gloss> for use in Korea.</item>
                            <item>Case II. All forces presently under <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1"
                                    >CINCFE</gloss> Command.</item>
                            <item>Case III. Same as Case II augmented (not before Spring 1953) as
                                follows: <list>
                                    <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                    <item>Ground forces: 82d Airborne Div and an addl Marine Div
                                        with its Marine Air Wing, plus addl <gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                                            >ROK</gloss> forces (2 Divs and 6 Rgts) as outlined in
                                        ur C 50459 and CX 50698.<note n="1" xml:id="d274fn1">These
                                            telegrams, dated June 19 and 23, 1952, respectively, are
                                            not printed.</note>
                                    </item>
                                    <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                    <item>Air Force forces: Two <gloss target="#t_MB1">MB</gloss>
                                        Wings now on standby, 3 Fighter-Bomber Wings, and sufficient
                                        troop carrier aircraft to provide required airlift.</item>
                                    <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                    <item>Naval forces: Two carriers, 1 battleship, 5 cruisers, 41
                                        destroyers, 1/3 Div amphibious lift (distribution of Naval
                                        forces between <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss> and
                                            <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> for course
                                        of action in Para 2<hi rend="italic">c</hi> above to be
                                        determined later).</item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div>
